The paper discusses training a deep neural network on a large dataset of natural images and videos, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of high-performance computing (HPC) architectures suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of Flickr as the source of the dataset suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as Flickr includes textual metadata associated with the images and videos.
